---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Disclaimer | Smesh.Dev" 
  description="Legal Disclaimer for Smesh.dev. Learn about warranties, third-party APIs, and AI chatbot limitations under BismillahTC Digital Services."
>
  <section class="site-shell py-16 md:py-24 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <span class="section-kicker">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="display-title text-[color:var(--ink)] text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight font-display border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
        Disclaimer
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-sans">
        Last Updated: June 2026 &mdash; Khanewal, Pakistan
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-655 font-sans font-light">
      <p>
        The terms of this disclaimer govern all information, templates, custom automation scripts, databases, and AI configurations provided on this website or delivered through consulting contracts by <strong>Smesh.dev</strong> (operated under <strong>BismillahTC Digital Services</strong>).
      </p>

      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">1. No Guarantees on Business Outcomes</h2>
        <p>
          While we build highly optimized, secure, and production-ready workflows (n8n, Supabase, chatbots, custom websites), Smesh.dev cannot guarantee specific business outcomes, timeline efficiencies, traffic increases, or financial returns. Business results depend entirely on your operational data, customer interaction quality, and how you manage and run the deployed systems.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">2. Third-Party Tools & API Services</h2>
        <p>
          Our integrations rely on third-party SaaS providers and cloud services (including, but not limited to, n8n, Supabase, OpenAI, Meta, WhatsApp, Vercel, and Twilio). 
        </p>
        <p>
          Smesh.dev provides no warranties (express or implied) regarding the operational uptime, future pricing, security compliance, or feature availability of these third-party platforms. Any system errors, downtime, or cost changes caused by these external platforms are not the responsibility of Smesh.dev.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">3. AI Chatbots & LLM Limitations</h2>
        <p>
          We construct AI chatbots and customer support pipelines using advanced semantic prompt designs and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). However, because these systems utilize large language models (LLMs), they have inherent limitations.
        </p>
        <p>
          AI agents can occasionally hallucinate, output incorrect details, or present outdated suggestions. Smesh.dev is not liable for customer support mistakes, communication errors, or database errors caused by automated AI replies. We recommend adding human moderation (human-in-the-loop) for high-impact business flows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">4. Scope of Support & Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          All systems are built and tested to meet client-approved specifications. Post-launch, technical support is limited to the agreed scope in the proposal and includes <strong>30 days of free support</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          After the 30-day support period, any troubleshooting, system revisions, API upgrades, or troubleshooting of third-party system outages will require a separate paid maintenance contract or hourly billing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          Smesh.dev and BismillahTC Digital Services will not be liable for any direct, indirect, special, or consequential losses, including lost revenue, loss of business data, database corruption, or system disruptions. You assume full operational responsibility for the systems once they are deployed to your active servers or cloud accounts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">6. General Information Only</h2>
        <p>
          The case studies, articles, blueprints, and database guides hosted on this site are for general educational purposes. They do not constitute professional, legal, or data compliance advice. It is your responsibility to verify that your data processing pipelines comply with local laws (such as Pakistan's Prevention of Electronic Crimes Act - PECA) or global rules (GDPR, HIPAA).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact Section -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t border-slate-200 pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">Questions?</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions regarding these disclaimers or want to discuss technical limits, please email:
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold">
          Email: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="text-[color:var(--accent-strong)] underline">{site.email}</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
